==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm|en}} ''semen'' "to seem, befit, be becoming" from {{etyl|non|en}} {{term|sœma||to conform to, beseem, befit|lang=non}} (> Danish {{term|sømme||beseem|lang=da}}) from {{term|sœmr||fitting, seemly|lang=non}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|sōmijaną||to unite, fit|lang=gem-pro}}, akin to Old Norse {{term|sómi|sōmi|honour|lang=non}} ( > archaic Danish {{term|somme||decent comportment|lang=da}}), {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|seman|sēman|to reconcile, bring an agreement|lang=ang}}, Old English {{term|som|sōm|agreement|lang=ang}}.

